<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> Each Member State shall ensure that, where an accident is caused in its territory by a vehicle normally based in the territory of another Member State, the national insurers' bureau shall, without prejudice to the obligation referred to in the first indent of Article 2 (2), obtain information: </inglise>
<eesti> Iga liikmesriik tagab, et juhul kui tema territooriumil p&otilde;hjustab &otilde;nnetuse s&otilde;iduk, mille p&otilde;hiasukoht on teise liikmesriigi territooriumil, teatatakse artikli 2 l&otilde;ike 2 esimeses taandes nimetatud kohustust piiramata liikluskindlustuse rahvuslikule b&uuml;roole j&auml;rgmised andmed: </eesti>
<inglise> - as to the territory in which the vehicle is normally based, and as to its registration mark, if any; </inglise>
<eesti> - territoorium, kus on s&otilde;iduki p&otilde;hiasukoht, ja v&otilde;imaluse korral s&otilde;iduki registreerimism&auml;rk; </eesti>
<inglise> - in so far as is possible, as to the details of the insurance of the vehicle, as they normally appear on the green card, which are in the possession of the person having custody of the vehicle, to the extent that these details are required by the Member State in whose territory the vehicle is normally based. </inglise>
<eesti> - v&otilde;imaluse korral s&otilde;iduki kindlustusega seotud &uuml;ksikasjad sellistena, nagu nad tavaliselt esitatakse rohelisel kaardil, mis kuulub s&otilde;iduki valdajale, kuiv&otilde;rd seda n&otilde;uab liikmesriik, mille territooriumil on s&otilde;iduki p&otilde;hiasukoht. </eesti>
<inglise> Each Member State shall also ensure that the bureau communicates this information to the national insurers' bureau of the State in whose territory the vehicle is normally based. </inglise>
