<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> Each Member State shall take all appropriate measures to ensure that vehicles normally based in the territory of a third country or in the non-European territory of a Member State entering the territory in which the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community is in force shall not be used in its territory unless any loss or injury caused by those vehicles is covered, in accordance with the requirements of the laws of the various Member States on compulsory insurance against civil liability in respect of the use of vehicles, throughout the territory in which the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community is in force. </inglise>
<eesti> Iga liikmesriik v&otilde;tab k&otilde;ik vajalikud meetmed tagamaks, et s&otilde;idukid, mille p&otilde;hiasukoht on kolmanda riigi territooriumil v&otilde;i liikmesriigi v&auml;ljaspool Euroopat asuval territooriumil ja mis sisenevad territooriumile, kus kehtib Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamisleping, kasutatakse tema territooriumil ainult juhul, kui selliste s&otilde;idukite tekitatavad kahjud on kaetud eri liikmesriikide mootors&otilde;idukite kasutamisega seotud tsiviilvastutuse kohustuslikku kindlustust k&auml;sitlevates &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uete kohaselt kogu territooriumil, kus kehtib Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamisleping. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 7 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 7 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Every vehicle normally based in the territory of a third country or in the non-European territory of a Member State must, before entering the territory in which the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community is in force, be provided either with a valid green card or with a certificate of frontier insurance establishing that the vehicle is insured in accordance with Article 6. </inglise>
<eesti> Enne sellisele territooriumile sisenemist, kus kehtib Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamisleping, peab k&otilde;igil s&otilde;idukitel, mille p&otilde;hiasukoht on kolmanda riigi territooriumil v&otilde;i m&otilde;ne liikmesriigi v&auml;ljaspool Euroopat paikneval territooriumil, olema kas kehtiv roheline kaart v&otilde;i piirikindlustuse sertifikaat, mis t&otilde;endab, et s&otilde;iduk on kindlustatud vastavalt artiklile 6. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> However, vehicles normally based in a third country shall be treated as vehicles normally based in the Community if the national bureaux of all the Member States severally guarantee, each in accordance with the provisions of its own national law on compulsory insurance, settlement of claims in respect of accidents occurring in their territory caused by such vehicles. </inglise>
<eesti> S&otilde;idukid, mille p&otilde;hiasukoht on kolmandas riigis, k&auml;sitatakse tavaliselt &uuml;henduses asuvate s&otilde;idukitena juhul, kui k&otilde;igi liikmesriikide rahvuslikud b&uuml;rood &uuml;hiselt garanteerivad iga&uuml;ks oma riigi sundkindlustust k&auml;sitlevate &otilde;igusaktide s&auml;tete kohaselt oma territooriumil selliste s&otilde;idukite p&otilde;hjustatud &otilde;nnetustest tulenevate n&otilde;uete lahendamise. </eesti>
